{
  "doc_id": "52746",
  "text": "Adiponectin is the most abundant adipose-specific protein. Its expression is reduced in obesity, insulin resistance, and type 2 diabetes; plasma concentrations are inversely related to body weight, especially visceral adiposity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Recent research indicates that adiponectin may have antiinflammatory, antiatherogenic, and antidiabetic properties [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Lower serum adiponectin concentrations are reported to be associated with coronary artery disease (6 -8) .",
